ZH: 他从小就显示出了很高的天资。
EN: He has shown great aptitude since he was young.

ZH: 她有很好的天资，学习起来特别容易。
EN: She has a great talent and finds learning very easy.

ZH: 这个孩子有天资出色，将来一定会成为一个优秀的音乐家。
EN: This child has exceptional talent and will surely become an excellent musician in the future.

ZH: 这位艺术家拥有天资，可以将一幅普通的画作变得独特而美丽。
EN: This artist possesses the talent to make an ordinary painting unique and beautiful.

ZH: 无论何种艺术形式，天资是最核心的因素之一。
EN: Regardless of the art form, talent is one of the most crucial factors.

ZH: 天资可以培养，但也需要不断努力和坚持。
EN: Talent can be nurtured, but it also requires continuous effort and perseverance.

ZH: 他的天资使他成为了这个领域的佼佼者。
EN: His talent has made him one of the top performers in this field.

ZH: 天资并不是决定成功的唯一因素，努力也是至关重要的。
EN: Talent is not the only factor that determines success; hard work is also crucial.

ZH: 她虽然有一些天资，但是她在这个项目上需要更多的训练和经验。
EN: Although she has some talent, she needs more training and experience for this project.

ZH: 这个小孩有很大的天资，但是他需要指导和引导来发展他的才能。
EN: This child has great potential, but he needs guidance and mentoring to develop his talents.

ZH: 即使有一般的天资，只要勤奋努力也能取得很大的进步。
EN: Even with average talent, great progress can be achieved through hard work and dedication.

ZH: 每个人都有自己的天资，只需要找到适合自己的领域去发展。
EN: Everyone has their own talents; it's just a matter of finding the right field to develop them in.

ZH: 这本书教给我们如何发掘和利用自己的天资。
EN: This book teaches us how to discover and utilize our own talents.

ZH: 别人的天资再好，也不能取代我们自己的努力。
EN: No matter how talented others may be, it cannot replace our own effort.

ZH: 有些人天资聪明，但是缺乏动力和毅力。
EN: Some people are intelligent, but lack motivation and perseverance.

ZH: 天资只是起点，成功需要更多的奋斗和坚持。
EN: Talent is just the starting point; success requires more hard work and perseverance.

ZH: 天资是一种资源，只有善加利用才能发挥最大的效果。
EN: Talent is a resource that can only be maximized through proper utilization.

ZH: 每个人的天资都有其独特之处，没有谁比谁更好或更差。
EN: Everyone's talents have their unique qualities; no one is better or worse than others.

ZH: 天资不同并不意味着某种才能的优越性，每个人都有自己的闪光点。
EN: Different talents do not imply the superiority of certain abilities; everyone has their own strengths.

ZH: 他的天资使他在艺术方面有着独到的见解和创造力。
EN: His talent gives him unique insights and creativity in the field of art.
